The paper deals with dynamic networks and communication failures, which are typical topics in distributed computing (cs.DC) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses message survivability and task solvability, which are related to algorithmic aspects of distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also considers synchronous and asynchronous models, which are relevant to systems and control theory (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT).
